---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'GeoBlue in Mexico', level: 2 },
  { id: 'blue-cross-advantage', text: 'Blue Cross Advantage', level: 2 },
  { id: 'mexico-network', text: 'Network Coverage in Mexico', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'vs-local-options', text: 'vs Mexican Insurers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'imss-combo', text: 'IMSS + GeoBlue Strategy', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-its-for', text: 'Who Should Choose GeoBlue', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Mexico', href: '/countries/mexico/insurance' },
  { title: 'GeoBlue Review', href: '/providers/geoblue' },
  { title: 'GeoBlue vs Aetna', href: '/compare/aetna-international-vs-geoblue' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'mexicoPrice', header: 'Mexico (Age 35)' },
  { key: 'usIncluded', header: 'US Coverage' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Voyager Essential', coverage: 'Inpatient + Emergency', mexicoPrice: '$155-210/mo', usIncluded: 'Full BCBS' },
  { plan: 'Voyager Choice', coverage: 'Essential + Outpatient', mexicoPrice: '$210-280/mo', usIncluded: 'Full BCBS' },
  { plan: 'Voyager Excel', coverage: 'Comprehensive + Maternity', mexicoPrice: '$280-370/mo', usIncluded: 'Full BCBS' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'factor', header: 'Factor' },
  { key: 'geoblue', header: 'GeoBlue' },
  { key: 'mexican', header: 'Mexican Insurers' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { factor: 'Monthly Cost (Age 35)', geoblue: '$210-280', mexican: '$120-180' },
  { factor: 'US Coverage', geoblue: '96% of US hospitals (BCBS)', mexican: 'Not available' },
  { factor: 'Network in Mexico', geoblue: 'Good', mexican: 'Extensive' },
  { factor: 'Deductible Type', geoblue: 'Annual', mexican: 'Per-illness (lifetime)' },
  { factor: 'Currency', geoblue: 'USD', mexican: 'MXN' },
  { factor: 'Mobile App', geoblue: 'Excellent', mexican: 'Varies' },
  { factor: 'Medical Evacuation', geoblue: 'Included', mexican: 'Usually not' },
  { factor: 'Portability', geoblue: 'Worldwide', mexican: 'Mexico only' },
];

const hospitalColumns = [
  { key: 'city', header: 'City' },
  { key: 'hospitals', header: 'Network Hospitals' },
  { key: 'directBilling', header: 'Direct Billing' },
];

const hospitalRows = [
  { city: 'Mexico City', hospitals: 'Hospital ABC, Médica Sur, Hospital Ángeles', directBilling: true },
  { city: 'Guadalajara', hospitals: 'Hospital San Javier, Hospital Puerta de Hierro', directBilling: true },
  { city: 'Monterrey', hospitals: 'Christus Muguerza, Hospital Zambrano Hellion', directBilling: true },
  { city: 'Puerto Vallarta', hospitals: 'Hospital CMQ, Hospiten', directBilling: true },
  { city: 'Los Cabos', hospitals: 'Hospiten Los Cabos, Hospital de Especialidades', directBilling: true },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="GeoBlue Health Insurance in Mexico"
  description="Guide to using GeoBlue in Mexico. Blue Cross Blue Shield network for US expats. Coverage, pricing, and how it compares to Mexican insurance."
  headline="GeoBlue Health Insurance in Mexico"
  subheadline="Blue Cross Blue Shield's international arm. Keep your familiar US network while enjoying life south of the border."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/mexico-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get a GeoBlue Mexico Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/geoblue"
>
  <h2 id="overview">GeoBlue in Mexico</h2>
  <p>
    GeoBlue is Blue Cross Blue Shield's international brand, designed specifically for Americans living abroad. For the massive community of US expats in Mexico—retirees in Lake Chapala, snowbirds in Puerto Vallarta, families in Mexico City—GeoBlue offers continuity with the healthcare system they already know.
  </p>
  <p>
    When you fly home for Thanksgiving or need to see a US specialist, your GeoBlue card works at 96% of US hospitals—the same Blue Cross network used by over 100 million Americans. No surprise networks, no coverage gaps.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">96%</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">US hospitals in network</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">1.7M+</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">International providers</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">190+</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Countries covered</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get a Mexico-Specific Quote"
    description="See what GeoBlue costs for Americans in Mexico."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/geoblue"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="blue-cross-advantage">Blue Cross Advantage</h2>
  <p>
    The core reason to choose GeoBlue for Mexico is the Blue Cross Blue Shield network:
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">US Network Benefits</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-blue-800">
        <li>96% of US hospitals in network</li>
        <li>Blue Cross negotiated rates</li>
        <li>Direct billing—no claims</li>
        <li>Familiar network for US care</li>
        <li>Keep relationships with US doctors</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Why It Matters in Mexico</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Medicare doesn't work abroad</li>
        <li>Visiting family? Covered.</li>
        <li>US specialists accessible</li>
        <li>Border emergencies handled</li>
        <li>Second opinions in the US</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-2">Border Resident Example</h3>
    <p class="text-green-800">
      Living in Tijuana? With GeoBlue, you could see your regular doctor at Hospital Ángeles in Tijuana, then walk across the border for a procedure at Scripps in San Diego—same insurance card, seamless coverage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h3>vs Other US Expat Options</h3>
  <p>
    GeoBlue, Aetna, and Cigna all serve US expats in Mexico. The key difference:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>GeoBlue:</strong> Blue Cross network (96% of US hospitals), US always included</li>
    <li><strong>Aetna:</strong> Aetna network, US always included, modular plans</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Cigna network, US is optional add-on (60-70% extra)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <a href="/compare/aetna-international-vs-geoblue">Compare GeoBlue vs Aetna</a> for a detailed breakdown.
  </p>

  <h2 id="mexico-network">Network Coverage in Mexico</h2>
  <p>
    GeoBlue contracts with 1.7 million+ providers in 190 countries. In Mexico, coverage focuses on major cities and popular expat areas.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={hospitalColumns} rows={hospitalRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Coverage by Region</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Mexico City:</strong> Strong network including ABC, Médica Sur, Ángeles hospitals</li>
    <li><strong>Guadalajara:</strong> Good coverage—serving Lake Chapala expats</li>
    <li><strong>Monterrey:</strong> Multiple hospital options</li>
    <li><strong>Beach towns:</strong> Coverage in Puerto Vallarta, Cancún, Los Cabos</li>
    <li><strong>Border cities:</strong> Plus seamless US access across the border</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>GeoBlue Mobile App</h3>
  <p>
    GeoBlue's app is excellent for finding care in Mexico:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>GPS-based provider search</li>
    <li>Filter by specialty and language</li>
    <li>English-speaking doctor finder</li>
    <li>Direct contact and directions</li>
    <li>Digital insurance card</li>
    <li>Claims submission from your phone</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Out-of-Network Care</h3>
  <p>
    You can see any licensed provider in Mexico. Mexican healthcare is affordable—paying out of pocket and claiming reimbursement is straightforward. GeoBlue reimburses at usual, customary, and reasonable (UCR) rates.
  </p>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    GeoBlue Voyager plans include US coverage—not an expensive add-on.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <em>Prices include worldwide coverage with full Blue Cross US access.</em>
  </p>

  <h3>Plan Recommendations for Mexico</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Voyager Essential:</strong> Hospital-focused. Good if you're healthy, using IMSS for routine care, and want catastrophic + US coverage.</li>
    <li><strong>Voyager Choice:</strong> Most popular. Includes outpatient, good balance of coverage and cost.</li>
    <li><strong>Voyager Excel:</strong> Comprehensive including maternity. Best for families or those wanting full coverage.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Deductible Options</h3>
  <p>
    Mexican healthcare is affordable. Consider:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Doctor visit: $30-60</li>
    <li>Specialist: $50-100</li>
    <li>Lab work: $20-50</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    A higher deductible ($2,000-5,000) can significantly reduce premiums. Pay routine care out of pocket in Mexico and use insurance for hospitals and US care.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Blue Cross Coverage in Mexico"
    description="Keep your familiar US network while living abroad."
    buttonText="Get Your Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/geoblue"
  />

  <h2 id="vs-local-options">vs Mexican Insurers</h2>
  <p>
    How does GeoBlue compare to Mexican insurance companies?
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Key Differences</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>US coverage:</strong> GeoBlue includes full Blue Cross US coverage. Mexican insurers don't cover the US at all—you'd need separate travel insurance for family visits.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Deductible structure:</strong> Mexican insurers use per-illness lifetime deductibles. GeoBlue uses annual deductibles that reset each year.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Medical evacuation:</strong> GeoBlue includes evacuation. Mexican insurers typically don't.
  </p>

  <h2 id="imss-combo">IMSS + GeoBlue Strategy</h2>
  <p>
    Many savvy expats combine IMSS and GeoBlue:
  </p>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">The Combination Approach</h3>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-blue-800">
      <li><strong>IMSS ($500/year):</strong> Routine care, prescriptions, basic backup</li>
      <li><strong>GeoBlue Essential ($155/mo):</strong> Private hospitals, US access, emergencies</li>
      <li><strong>Total: ~$285/month</strong> for comprehensive Mexico + Blue Cross coverage</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h3>When to Use Each</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>IMSS:</strong> Generic medications, routine checkups, basic care</li>
    <li><strong>GeoBlue:</strong> Private hospitals, English-speaking doctors, US trips, emergencies</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    IMSS is so affordable (~$40/month for under-60s) that it's worth having as a backup and for routine care, even with GeoBlue.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who Should Choose GeoBlue</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Ideal For</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
        <li>US citizens in Mexico</li>
        <li>Those familiar with Blue Cross</li>
        <li>Expats who visit the US regularly</li>
        <li>People who want largest US network</li>
        <li>Those who value excellent mobile app</li>
        <li>Border residents</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Consider Alternatives</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Non-US citizens (can't purchase)</li>
        <li>Those who never visit the US</li>
        <li>Budget-conscious (IMSS cheaper)</li>
        <li>Wanting largest Mexican network</li>
        <li>Settled permanently in Mexico</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <h3>Do I need to be a US citizen for GeoBlue?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes. GeoBlue requires US citizenship or permanent residency with US ties. It's designed specifically for Americans abroad.
  </p>

  <h3>Does GeoBlue replace Medicare?</h3>
  <p>
    GeoBlue provides coverage abroad that Medicare doesn't offer. Many expats keep Medicare Part A (free if you qualify) as backup if they return to the US permanently, but use GeoBlue for actual healthcare in Mexico and when visiting the US.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I use GeoBlue and IMSS together?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes. Many expats enroll in IMSS (~$500/year) for routine care, then use GeoBlue for private hospitals, US visits, and major medical. It's a cost-effective combination.
  </p>

  <h3>How does the Blue Cross network work in Mexico?</h3>
  <p>
    The Blue Cross network is primarily a US benefit. In Mexico, GeoBlue has their own international network. You get the best of both: Blue Cross in the US and GeoBlue's network in Mexico.
  </p>

  <h3>What about medical evacuation?</h3>
  <p>
    GeoBlue includes medical evacuation coverage. If you're in a smaller Mexican town and need specialized care, they can evacuate you to Mexico City, the US, or wherever appropriate.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready for Coverage in Mexico?"
    description="Get a personalized GeoBlue quote for your situation."
    buttonText="Get Your Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/geoblue"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Network availability, pricing, and coverage terms change. We are not insurance brokers. Verify all information with GeoBlue before making decisions.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
